{"nodes":[{"nodeID":"763","text":"The law must be abrogated","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:57"},{"nodeID":"764","text":"California 's law extends the time in which prosecution is allowed","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:57"},{"nodeID":"765","text":"California 's law authorizes prosecutions that the passage of time has previously barred","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:57"},{"nodeID":"766","text":"California 's law was enacted after prior limitations periods for Stogner's alleged offenses had expired","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"767","text":"Such features produce the kind of retroactivity that the Constitution forbids","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"768","text":"If a law is not constitutional it must be abrogated","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"769","text":"the law threatens the kinds of harm that the Clause (of the Constitution) seeks to avoid","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"770","text":"If a law is against a clause of the Constitution the law is forbidden by the Constitution","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"771","text":"the Clause protects liberty by preventing governments from enacting statutes with  manifestly unjust and oppressive   retroactive effects. Calder v. Bull 3 Dall. 386 391","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"772","text":"The law has  manifestly  unjust and oppressive   retroactive effects","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"773","text":"the law falls literally within the categorical descriptions of ex post facto laws that Justice Chase set forth more than 200 years ago in Calder v. Bull","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"775","text":"Ex post fact laws are not constitutional","type":"I","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:19:58"},{"nodeID":"1329","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:21:49","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"1330","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:21:49","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"1331","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:21:50","scheme":"Example"},{"nodeID":"1332","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:21:50","scheme":"EstablishedRule"},{"nodeID":"1333","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:21:50","scheme":"VerbalClassification"},{"nodeID":"1334","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:21:51","scheme":"VerbalClassification"},{"nodeID":"1335","text":"RA","type":"RA","timestamp":"2012-04-12 18:21:51","scheme":"VerbalClassification"}],"edges":[{"edgeID":"1217","fromID":"764","toID":"1329","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1218","fromID":"1329","toID":"772","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1219","fromID":"765","toID":"1330","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1220","fromID":"1330","toID":"772","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1221","fromID":"766","toID":"1331","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1222","fromID":"1331","toID":"772","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1223","fromID":"767","toID":"1332","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1224","fromID":"768","toID":"1332","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1225","fromID":"1332","toID":"763","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1226","fromID":"769","toID":"1333","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1227","fromID":"770","toID":"1333","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1228","fromID":"1333","toID":"767","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1229","fromID":"771","toID":"1334","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1230","fromID":"772","toID":"1334","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1231","fromID":"1334","toID":"769","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1232","fromID":"773","toID":"1335","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1233","fromID":"775","toID":"1335","formEdgeID":null},{"edgeID":"1234","fromID":"1335","toID":"767","formEdgeID":null}]}